	      What would the patient's drug concentration be if the delivered concentration were a ramp?
	      More precisely, if it were
	      <m:math>
            <m:apply><m:times/>
              <m:ci><m:msub><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mi>d</m:mi></m:msub></m:ci>
              <m:ci>t</m:ci>
	          <m:apply><m:ci type="fn">u</m:ci><m:ci>t</m:ci></m:apply>
            </m:apply>
          </m:math>?
	      </item>
	      
	      <item>
	      A clever doctor wants to have the flexibility to slow down or speed up the patient's drug concentration.
	      In other words, the concentration is to be
	      <m:math>
          <m:apply><m:times/>
            <m:ci><m:msub><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mi>p</m:mi></m:msub></m:ci>
            <m:apply><m:minus/>
              <m:cn>1</m:cn>
              <m:apply><m:exp/>
                <m:apply><m:minus/>
                  <m:apply><m:times/>
